caption: Food so so.  Portion size not great.  If hungry, probably try another place.
Great pad thai. Great thai tea. I love this little restaurant.
Bangkok kitchen is open for takeout. Their dishes are wonderful,  you choose the level of spice. Cannot ask for better Thai food and the owners are genuinely nice people!
Got takeout from here and enjoyed it! Had drunken noodles with fried tofu. Great flavor, and really liked the texture and the way they cooked the tofu.

The best Thai restaurant in Omaha. Their fried rice is made perfectly! At every other restaurant it’s too goey and sticky or too hard, but at Bangkok they get it just right! All their dishes are good. I haven’t tried a dish I haven’t liked from their menu. Also, the staff is super friendly and make the place feel very welcoming.
Best pad thai in the world
thai food... so delicious. certainly worth a return visit. food and feeling reminds me of kansas city.
Best Thai in Omaha with the most hospitable staff.

Great food and friendly, family run business, make this a great place for your takeout, especially during the pandemic. Worth it to walk five minutes there or to drive in and pick-up. Here is to 20 more years in business!
I have never been disappointed at this restaurant. We love the yellow curry and the tom kha
My favorite Thai food in Omaha
Great portions, excellent flavor, and reasonable prices.
Great food for a reasonable price.  Fifth time here.  Different menu items every time.
Best Thai food I've ever had
Best Thai in Omaha
Always friendly. Love the food. Hard to go wrong with any choice but I especially enjoy the Pad Won Sen.
Our favorite Thai restaurant in Omaha.
Basil Chicken stir fry wasn't great.  Pad Thai was fine
outstanding - a rare find in downtown Omaha with a fantastic menu selection, service and food

If you’ve never been here this is about to be your new favorite Thai restaurant. Get their pad Thai! Best pad Thai I’ve ever had. No question, no competition, Nobody else comes close. You’ve got me as a life long customer. Can’t come to Omaha without stopping by. If you think you “know” the best Thai restaurant in Nebraska and you already have a favorite but haven’t been here yet... shut up and go here right now because your opinion is about to change! The business owner is always there and it shows with the quality of the food ❤️❤️❤️❤️
Happiness all around.  10min COOK 10min HOME 10min GONE

I tried the Red Curry with tofu and it was pretty good. The servings are pretty small compared to other Thai restaurants- and there were very few pieces of tofu. The only reason I’m rating so high is because the flavor of the red curry was extremely good. They really nailed it there. Pretty good overall!
Delicious and delightful date with my love💞.  We had the place mostly to ourselves because it was an odd time of day.  It is a tad hard to find.
My favorite Thai place in town.  Extremely friendly staff. The food is always delicious. Able to accommodate gluten free dietary needs! I could eat here every day.

I really LOVE their curries, all of them are very good. We drove 100 miles just to have some of their curries. Hubby likes the green , sometimes the red and I enjoy both the green and yellow.  Their portions are quite generous and I their service is superb.
It's bangin!
Best pad thai in town!

I do not care too much for their very hot spicy oriental food but I love the owners I've known them forever and you're so kind of nice to me I love their chai tea and the egg rolls and when the owner's wife makes me homemade cream puffs she is the best thank you
Great food and service!!
Great for eat-in and carry-out. Affordable comfort foods and the fried/soft tofu is great.  Very few dishes on the menu that I don't love. Staff are polite and friendly.
The panang curry was very good.  A well run family business.
The food was great, and the service was decent.
My favourite is Mercy thai ..bankok is 2nd
Great food! Great service! Family owned and operated!
No frills here, but great price and excellent chicken pad thai.

After trying to decide on dinner, my lady and I agreed on Thai, and Bangkok kitchen was our mendl decision. It was one of the best Thai restaurants I've ever had, let alone in Omaha or Nebraska. We even took some to go back home to Lincoln. Will definitely be back, and DEFINITELY recommend!
The food, particularly the curry and crab rangoon is amazing! I'm never disappointed!
Good food. Very nice people.
They use to have flavorful dishes. I ordered Red curry and Tom is Kai Soup. Lacking taste. They must have a different cook now.
Great food
All the food was authentic and exceptionally good. Just needs more rice is all.

Ordered the Pad Kua Gai with beef. The food came out very quickly. I ended up ordering a second plate because it was very good but not sufficiently filling (it was the only thing I ordered and I was very hungry). One of my lunch guests ordered a different dish with a much bigger portion that maybe could have been enough. I would definitely go back again and probably get the same dish but also try an appetizer to go with it
Great food!! Love this place:)
Refusing to meet my needs
The Chicken Pad Thai, crab rangoon, fried spring rolls, dipping sauces are absolutely wonderful. I love their Thai tea as well!!! Yes...seconds please!!!

Good food, simple decor. Took awhile to get menus etc. The Thai tea is to die for... could be addictive 😄 I had chicken pad thai.  The noodles were thin type. You are asked spice level... 0 - 10. Tasty. My family had Ginger chicken & Sweet and Sour w/ fried tofu. The fresh spring rolls were light & filled with lettuce and veggies. 3 rolls cut in half easy to share. The dipping sauce was a delicious sweet chili type.

Been my go-to for nearly twenty years. Always fresh. Best pad Thai, crab rangoon hands down. You know what? It's impossible to specify... it's ALL good. Go to 19th and Farnam, find the yellow door. Trust me, you'll be glad you did.
Delicious. Affordable. Fast. I will absolutely be back.
Good food, authentic Thai cuisine, they treat you like family 👍👍👍👍👍
Excellent prices. Good food. Average portions. Great flavor. I'd recommend!
Very authentic Thai food. The medium Spicer level was very spicy, should have asked for mild.
Good food, friendly staff. Really enjoyed our time there!
Some of the best Thai in Omaha. Been going there for years and the pad Thai is by far one of my favorites.b
Great food
Love it!.. I love the chicken skewers and a side of sticky rice 😍😍😍.. simple yet yummy food.
Love it!
Very yummy. So good,  my Thai ate all hers and ordered 2 extra meals Togo for lunch the next day.
Their yellow curry is really good.
Loved the pad Thai and the Thai iced tea!
Whatever you do - do not order coffee - it is an instant mix of warm water and instant coffee without creamer. My first fake coffee in over 12 years ... Horrible.
If you have a Thai food craving and you can't escape downtown, it will do. Small, quaint, fast service.
Pad Thai is my favorite food so I try it every place I visit. There's is one of my favorites.
Best ever pad thai in omaha!
Been going there for almost two decades.  No other place compares.
This place is my new favorite Thai restaurant. Flavorful, fast, big menu. Everything I've tried is great. Service is friendly and prompt. I wish I would have know abour this place years ago!
First time here. Had an Amazing time with my bestie! Food, atmosphere and service was excellent! I will definitely be going back.

I have been going to this place since I was a little girl, and I can say nothing but great things about it! The food is great, service is fast, staff are always friendly, and its family run, so thats a plus! The owner Victor has always been a delight to be around; he is nothing but welcoming from the minute you walk into the door. This is BY FAR the BEST thai food in omaha; there is NO comparison. If you are looking for a great thai restaurant, dont even hesitate to make this restaurant your first choice❗
The waitress is so sweet and place is clean. I give 5 star for that and 4 star for the food. The price is affordable.
Pros: Great food, served fast.  Cons: Below par customer service
Decent food,  not as rich, 'tasty' as some places in Kansas City that we like but altight.
First visit last night. Ordered my Thai favorites. Tom Kai Gai was just as good as my past experiences in NY and San Francisco. I asked for 7 of 10 on the spicy heat and that was plenty.
Great food at decent price
This is my favorite place forever and ever. Amazing food! Amazing staff! Great dining experiences every single time I've gone! Best Thai tea and tom kah soup IN TOWN!
I eat Thai food everywhere I travel.  I feel proud and unbiased to say Bangkok Kitchen is one of the best anywhere.
Basic menu with good fare

Tried this place today for a late lunch. It was very speedy and I appreciated the heater by my table. Had a friend in town this week and ate out a lot, and many places were very very cold. Was nice to not be cold while eating.  My friend had the pad Thai. It was simple with good flavor. I tried the broccoli chicken hoping that it would be like this one from a place that closed a few years ago that I loved. The flavors were the same and the sauce was just a little thicker but still was quite good. The portions were a bit small compared to other places but was still plenty of food to eat.  We will be back again to try some other things next time we are in Omaha. We have tried about 5 different Thai food places in the area and this is our favorite one. We had tried another place a few days before and while it was pretty tasty it had been very very oily. This was tasty and not oily at all.
Excellent flavor and pleasant setting.
I love this place, they’re always super quick and the food is fantastic.
Good food. Cozy and authentic ambiance.
Not so great..
Service was a little slow but food was delicious and the environment was peaceful.
Thai tea was super tasty. Got some delicious spring rolls and an awesome noodle dish. Definitely recommend

I have been coming here for years, since they were known as Bangkok Cuisine and had a small lunch buffet...Victor is usually running the register and always has a smile and a few laughs for his customers and regulars...the chef is an extremely nice lady who has a ready laugh and totally knows what I'm ordering every time lol...My go to dish is the Kao Kai Fu and it's been perfect every time...BK will continue to get my business for years to come...
Great food. Great service. Great price. Triple threat. Man I stumbled upon this gem and i sure am happy that I did. Thank you Bangkok kitchen! (Try the son in law eggs)
Decent Thai food.

Service was a step above terrible, food was quick but small portion and not what I’d expect. When ordering a curry, it’s typically served in a bowl as it’s base is coconut milk but this was not the case. We also ordered crab rations which were flat and had very little substance. Not what I expected from reading other reviews noting this as best Thai in town. I wouldn’t recommend unless truly craving Thai

Why is this place not more expensive!? It is amazing and I'm addicted. I eat here once a week. I see the owner more often than I see my own mother.  Do yourself a favor and get a thai tea with your drunken noodles.
Friendly, Quick, Good Quality. I go there about once every other week, sometimes more often
Love the atmosphere. Not the food as much. Salaween Thai is better in my opinion.
One of the best Thai places in Omaha.
Great every time! Great prices!
The best Thai food
Super bomb phad thai and the crab rangoons are the best i've ever had - EVER.
Excellent place to eat for Lunch or dinner, staff is Beautiful very accommodating
Small friendly place. Love it and eat here regularly.

Amazing taste but beware for the price you pay (I paid ten with tax for the green curry)portions are small. Salween Thai green curry tasted just as good but you got a way bigger bowl for ten bucks. When I was asking questions my waiter a young guy was extremely impatient. Not impressed with their service or portions. Delicious food though.
Wonderful,  yummy food!
The place all Thai food is judged against. 10 years later the food is still amazing.
The pad thai is fantastic.
Best authentic Chicken Pad Thai and we make a point to eat at this restaurant every time we visit Omaha!

Possibly some of the best Thai food in town! I have had the Curry and Pad Thai, and both were incredible. It seems to have authentic flavors and ingredients. Prices are very reasonable, so it is nice for lunches away from work. The staff are always very friendly and attentive.
Ok Thai food. I ordered hot, but not Thai hot. It wasn't hot at all.
Fantastic yellow painted door

The best Thai food in Omaha and in all 6 states I’ve lived in. Every single dish is a mouthgasm and I’ve tried almost everything on the menu by now. It’s my most favorite restaurant to eat at and I would come here every single day if I could. Anyone who hasn’t tried their amazing food is missing out. Not to mention, the family that runs this place is kind, caring and worth supporting

The service is pretty quick. The food tasted pretty good. The only reason I have gave this a 3 star rating is because of the sticky rice side that I ordered. It was hard and dry by the time it came out. Like it was sitting out for a while. Other than that, I had a decent experience.

What should I say? They use prepackaged dried noodles to make their drunken noodles. In my books, that's nowhere close to "fresh!" Barely any chicken with their stir fry; you might as well call it a vegetarian option. If this place was in Seattle it'll be out of business in no time. Hot garbage, lame food, avoid at all costs.
Cant stop thinking of my meal! Sad because I live in North Dakota and I don't think there will be a thai restaurant that will be anywhere close to this place!
Really awesome food.  Super clean and simple.  Best crab rangoon ever.  Very nice experience.
Great food every time I'm in town and friendly staff.
I went for the first time this week and got the garlic chicken. I asked for a 2 and felt like it was maybe a 5. Still good and quick service which I need on a lunch hour. I would go back.
Pad Thai noodles were great.
Good food
Me and my husband really loved the food. Everyone was so nice and friendly.  Deffenitly coming back here.
Incredible food! Loved the atmosphere and the staff was friendly.
Great food

We have been coming here for years, it's our favorite Thai place,  close to our house,  inexpensive,  great service and the best food. ..I have tried lots of stuff on the menu and it's all good.   We will keep coming regularly!
Food was delicious and came out very quickly!
Great food
A bit of a tight fit and some waiting involved, but the food is definitely worth it

One of my downtown lunch staples. Small and clean. Very few employees and food cooked to order so you might have to wait a little but its always worth it. I can vouch for the Cashew Chicken and Beef Broccoli. My son raves about the curry. Each item’s spice level can be adjusted to taste, 1 through 10.
Amazing pad thai
Love their food!
Good service, great food!
Quiet. Great service.  Original, authentic food.  Loved it!
Food is great. Service is good. It's very busy at lunchtime on weekdays and they need more waitstaff.

The steamed fish and crab rangoon from Bangkok Kitchen was some of the best food I’ve ever eaten. Fresh vegetables and tender fish, speedy service and great customer service. I plan to become a regular & stop in whenever I’m visiting town.
Great unique cuisine! They have high chairs and were very gracious about having a messy baby in such a clean and dignified restaurant.
Bold flavors ! Great prices,try something different you will be glad.

Bangkok has the absolute best Thai food in Omaha! Not to mention the best price point! I have yet to find a better Pad Thai dish in Omaha! (And I've tried almost every Thai restaurant here). You won't be disappointed!
Pad Thai was good but the fresh spring rolls lacks meat so not impressive
Really nice atmosphere, great Thai food, superb service.
Best Thai in town, hands down.  Food is exactly like some of the best in Thailand.

This place is a very special restaurant, family owned and staffed, food is excellent and reasonably priced. I must dine in at least once a month, and more often (anytime I am in town, but worth a drive for this food).

*Okay this review is for a Thai restaurant not ADT. Someone keeps changing the business name on Google.  ...pretty good after the reopen. They probably use less vegetables than other places (as a proportion of the dish) and more oil than other places.  Posting menu photos since there doesn't appear to be any other availability online.

Great Thai place close to downtown. It’s a bit of a hike, but some coworkers and I make this a regular place to eat during the warmer months. I’ve enjoyed both the broccoli beef and the red curry. The rangoon and egg rolls are also well liked.
One of my favorite restaurants. The food comes promptly. Great thai iced tea!!! Friendliest staff downtown.

Very nice small restaurant downtown.. perfect for intimate dining, specializing in Thai rice dishes.  Lot of options on Curry.. i had the Garlic Chicken and it was delicious... Service needs work, but food makes up for it...
I am Thai and this is my favorite restaurant in Omaha. They can actually make dishes outside their menu if you have any personal favorite dishes.
Good food. Friendly owner. We will be back!
Food was cooked fresh by the owner. Great low key restaurant.
awesome food
The food is great.... more over service is outstanding Even if there is a wait,, don't miss out for great food and gracious people

The food here is always good and if sweet and spicy are your two favorite things you will definitely enjoy this place.thai ice tea is always a good with spicy food .my favorite dish is the pork panang.the drunken noodles are also really good.they let you pick how spicy you want your food.8 is usually good for me 10 would probably be taken as a challenge
Great place to get takeout.
Descent food, no great ambience, overpriced!
Great Food
Well if you're in the mood for Thai food it is an okay place.
Great pad thai.  If you are going for lunch during the week then give yourself plenty of time since they can get a lot of orders all at once.
The best.
Service was fast (less than 10 minutes) and friendly. Pictured below is the sweet and sour chicken.

It does not matter what you order it will be delicious! I have been eating here my entire life. Not once have I been disappointed with anything on or off the menu. This is the best place for Thai Food in Omaha (certain dishes are better at other places but all around this is by far the best).
Great place run by great people. Consistently high quality.

Perhaps I'm biased being from a different area and just visiting, but this place is decent, but not as great as everyone makes it out to be.  I read the reviews and thought that this might be a great place, but I was disappointed.  I ordered curry and fried rice and I was told it was $23.  I thought that was a little high but that maybe they would give generous portions, but they did not.  I got a cup and a half of fried rice and half a cup of curry (approximately).  What there was of the curry and rice was good, which is why I give this place 2 stars, but definitely lacking in portion size.
Great service yummy food ! Poor man's noodles best in the world
Best Thai food I've had in Omaha! Closest to the food we enjoyed in Thailand!

Bangkok Kitchen is the best Thai food in Omaha. I lived in Phuket for 10 months and struggled to find great Thai food here in Omaha. Finding Bangkok Kitchen was a relief. The food is excellent, and the owners are very kind people. I highly recommend the Panang Chicken and their Tom Yum soups. The spice level goes from 1 to 10, and I usually do a 7. I really love spicy food, so most people will probably be happy with a 2. Without a doubt the best Thai food in Omaha!
Always DELICIOUS ..I have been coming here for 10 plus years food is amazing authentic family owned.. Lovely family!!
Food is good, fast and staff very friendly.  Not my favorite Thai place, but good.  I do love the son-in-law eggs.
Excellent food. Good atmosphere. They recently renovated the place which looks very nice.
Very friendly service and quality food, just a little pricy for the portion size.

Super good pad thai. So good. What else needs to be said? I guess the only down side is no free refills on pop (if you care about that kind of thing), and the TV is sometimes turned to MSNBC. You might have to eat while watching skinny Al Sharpton (never helps digestion).
Smaller portions than I was expecting, but the food is great!
Victor and his family provide excellent food at a low cost.  I had gotten take out there one a week for 3 years and every time is was excellent!
I love Thai foods here. Very authentic!
Family owned restaurant. Best Thai food I have ever eaten!  Each dish is prepared to order, which could explain why some commented that it can be slow, but my experience has only been great service.
Love love love
Amazing  Kao Tom Gai and egg rolls!
Best Pad Thai hands down!
Best Thai food in town

Best Thai food place!¡ My coworkers and I love this place and their owners. They're so nice and accommodate our needs, and everyone's around. They have great rapport w their regulars. And the food is TO DIE FOR!¡
Very friendly and fast service.  The food is awesome & always fresh.

I have been going to Bangkok since I was little and I have never had Pad Thai as good as theirs. Many of my fondest memories include my mother bringing me home Pad Thai. It's a great place to eat and I have always felt welcome and at home when dining there.
I always regret not getting more of their thin egg rolls, they're just so easy to eat like popcorn.
***It's closed until further notice.*** Tried to go there for dinner.
This isn't meant to be a bad review, there is a sign in the window that's says "closed until further notice" just a heads up.
Excellent food.  They even made an off the menu item for a friend's birthday party.
Great pad thai, spring rolls might be the best I have ever had.
More authentic than your average Thai place. Flavors are pretty good except a tad too sweet for my tastes (though, again, not as sweet as the average Thai restaurant).
I had the Thai Fried Rice. It was good. Though my favorite Thai restaurant in Omaha is still Thai Kitchen.
Delicious and great service !

Courteous staffs, but food is not Authentic Thai (i was living in Asia and Thai food is my favorite, so i can tell). and they way they charge you seems very unfair. You see a price in the Menu and they charge you differently and they have their own justification. Before this I always been going to "Salween Thai Restaurant" at Radial Highway. Their food is way better and prices are way more reasonable and transparent. If you go at lunch or dinner time to "Salween Thai", restaurant is full of customers vs Bangkok Cuisine is at Downtown (Better location), but not food, not services, nor the prices are compatitive. I will stick to "Salween Thai".
Best in Omaha hands down
Not bad. Came in from Minnesota. Spring Rolls were really yummy. The soup was pretty delicious.

One of my favorite places in town, when I was in college I used to frequent this place all of the time.  The prices are fair and so is the owner, a very kind man.  The service is wonder and the food is very good as well.

The food here is not bad. It's not authentic Thai but still fine. What I don't like about here is the service from the young guy with glasses. He treated other tables well, but he did not do it for mine. The service was slow and when I asked for the check, he talked to me in an impolite tone and handed me the check by sliding it on my table. I'm not being sensitive, I have been here many times and the service from this guy is not good. I would like to ask them to educate their waiter.
Poor man noodles, spicy level 15. Best entree

If you want unlimited mediocre Thai food this might be a good place for you (lunch buffet). I would rather enjoy my Thai food though, and this place was a disappointment. The Tom Kah soup tasted like rotten fish, and the Yellow Curry was still only mediocre. Thai Orchids in LaVista is the best Thai restaurant in Omaha, and if you do not agree, you are wrong.

I tried the jungle curry and .... "Welcome to the jungle.......".  The soup and egg rolls were also excellent.  Very reasonably priced as well.  My meal was prepared as a 5 on the spicy scale (1-10) and it was hot.  I could not stop eating it though.  Can't wait to stop again.
My favorite Thai food restaurant in Omaha. Personal service and great food!

My favorite Thai restaurant in the metro,  spicy level 10 means spicy level 10. As for the service?  Simply the best. I left my credit card once and it was a few months before I was able to make it back.  had no idea where I had left it so just cancelled my card and moved on. Guy came over to take our order and brought the card with him. With a wink he said I should be more careful with it.

I eat here at least once a week, and it is great Thai.  Some have complained about the spiciness of the food, but most Thai is spicy.  You can choose anywhere between 1 and 10 to create your own spice level.  I have always thought the food is top notch, although you have to remember that this is a "hole in the wall" place.  Speaking of that, the inside is not going to be fancy.  And service may be hit-or-miss because the owner's family work as the servers, and some are better at it than others.  That being said, I've never had anyone be rude to me--actually quite the opposite.  If you like Thai food and can do without fancy trappings, this is a place you should check out.
I go out of my way to eat at this little gem! If you want an authentic experience and great food this is the place!

I've had Thai in many cities, including Portland, Seattle, and San Francisco, and I still have to say I love this place. Not only do we go back there every time we're in Omaha, but we've been known to make excuses to visit Omaha just to go here for Thai. We love it, our kids love it, and the owners are wonderful. Highly, highly recommended.
